                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-284-off1441 t18300916-284-crimeloc1444"></join>. On the 7th of September the two prisoners came together, to pawn a gown, at half-past eight o'clock in the evening - I saw Elizabeth leave the counter; she seemed to move about; she said to Francis once or twice,</p>
               <p>"Go, Jem" - that excited my suspicion; she stood against a partition - I went to serve another person; she then stood against the place where this shift was pinned - I went up, and she was covering this boy with her clothes; he had the shift under his frock.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-284-person2361">
                  GEORGE 
                  OVERS
               <interp inst="t18300916-284-person2361" type="surname" value="OVERS"></interp>
